## 2. What is Tableau? 📈  
Tableau is a powerful and leading data visualization tool.  

It allows you to intuitively **click, drag, and drop data elements** to explore and interrogate your data.

In other words:  
👉 Tableau makes it easy to build beautiful, interactive visualizations from raw data.

---

## 3. Why use Tableau? 🚀  
Tableau is designed for a wide range of business users and non-technical audiences, but it also provides access to deep computational ability for advanced data analytics.

### ✨ Key Advantages:
- 🔄 Flexible — you can work with many different data sources  
- 🧠 Intuitive — visual cues and icons make navigation easier  
- 🖱️ Fast prototyping — drag-and-drop makes dashboard creation quick (hours or days instead of weeks)  

### 📊 End-to-end workflow in one tool:
You can:
- Frame the business question you want to answer  
- Import and clean data  
- Analyze and visualize data  
- Make business decisions  
- Present insights  

All within Tableau!

---

## 4. Who uses Tableau? 👥  
Tableau enables anyone to ask questions about their data.

Common job roles include:
- 📊 Data Analyst  
- 💼 Business Analyst  
- 🔍 Analytics Consultant  

Basically, anyone who wants to analyze or visualize data can benefit from Tableau.

